ecuparam.name: IAM (4-byte)*
ecuparam.desc: E31-KCA = (KA (max) map value * IAM) + FBKC + FLKC. Total Timing = KCA + base timing + timing compensations

ecuparam.name: Engine Load (4-Byte)*
ecuparam.desc: E32-This is the current engine load (g/rev) as determined by the ECU.

ecuparam.name: CL/OL Fueling*
ecuparam.desc: E33-Fuel system status. [8 = CL (normal)][10 = OL (normal)][7 = OL insufficient ECT][14 = OL due to system failure]

ecuparam.name: Throttle Plate Opening Angle (4-byte)*
ecuparam.desc: E38-Actual throttle plate opening percentage. More accurate than the standard Throttle Opening Angle % SSM parameter.

ecuparam.name: Feedback Knock Correction (4-byte)*
ecuparam.desc: E39-This is the temporary negative correction to timing advance in response to what the ECU perceives as knock.

ecuparam.name: Fine Learning Knock Correction (4-byte)*
ecuparam.desc: E41-Current learned correction that is being applied which is stored and applied across specific load and rpm ranges.

ecuparam.name: A/F Learning #1 A (Stored)*
ecuparam.desc: E44-A/F learned correction to CL and OL fueling across specific air flow ranges based on short-term A/F Correction witin range.

ecuparam.name: A/F Learning #1 B (Stored)*
ecuparam.desc: E45-A/F learned correction to CL and OL fueling across specific air flow ranges based on short-term A/F Correction witin range.

ecuparam.name: A/F Learning #1 C (Stored)*
